Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
The main goal in crossing the street is to be alive by the end of it. First and foremost, this means always crossing with an adult; never cross the street alone. When you have  your adult in tow, look both ways, up and down each side of the street. Make sure no cars are coming or that they are all stopped and then you can cross.